<chapter><title>URL specification for media access</title>

<section><title>Introduction</title>
<para>
The URL is a string representation for a media location.
It specifies the physical access to the media. It does not
make any assumptions about the media content.
</para>
</section>
<section><title>General layout</title>
<para>
A media URL consists of four parts
<itemizedlist>
  <listitem><para>Media Type</para>
    <para>Allowed types are cd, dvd, nfs, ftp, dir, disk, http</para>
    <para>Types are not case sensitive</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem><para>Media device or server</para>
    <para>Some media types allow a comma-separated list of devices,
      e.g. cd or dvd ("/dev/cdrom,/dev/cdrecorder")</para>
  </listitem>
  <listitem><para>Path on device or server</para></listitem>
  <listitem><para>options</para>
    <para>this is a type-specific comma-separated list of 'type=value'
       pairs, e.g. 'user=ftp,pass=ftp' for ftp access</para>
  </listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>
Type, device, path, and options are separated by a colon (':')
</para>
<para>
Type, device, and path are mandatory. Options can be left out.
</para>
</section>
<section><title>CD access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for CD access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    cd:/dev/cdrom:/suse
    cd:/dev/cdrom,/dev/cdrecorder:/suse
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>
<section><title>DVD access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for DVD access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    dvd:/dev/dvd:/suse
    dvd:/dev/dvd,/dev/dvd1:/suse
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>
<section><title>NFS access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for NFS access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    nfs:nfs.suse.de:/var/share/SuSE-Linux/CD1
    nfs:12.34.56.78:/
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>
<section><title>FTP access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for FTP access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    ftp:ftp.suse.com:/pub/suse/i386/8.0/suse
    ftp:you.suse.de:/pub/suse/updates/i386/7.3:user=anon,pass=ftp,proxy=proxy.suse.de,proxyport=4242,proxytype=http
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>
<section><title>Directory access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for DIR access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    dir::/local/directory
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>
<section><title>Disk partition access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for DISK access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    disk:/dev/hda3:/suse/CD1
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>
<section><title>HTTP access</title>
<example>
  <title>URL for HTTP access</title>
  <para>
  <screen width="60">
    http:maintenance.suse.de:/restricted/login/suse:user=sample,pass=word42
  </screen>
  </para>
</example>
</section>

</chapter>

